Muziq Rigor

Muziq Rigor is a Lua command-line application written to validate metadata
usage within a folder, based on defined rules.

Features:
 - Runs on babies, like everything else I write.
 - Supports the FLAC and Ogg file formats.
 - Supports reading VorbisComment metadata.

Requirements:
 - Lua 5.1
 - vstruct 1.1 (included) (http://www.funkyhorror.net/toxicfrog/projects/vstruct/)
 - LuaFileSystem 1.2.1 or newer (http://keplerproject.github.com/luafilesystem/)
